All Sabine Parish Schools will open on Tuesday, September 8, 2020. Pre-K through 5th Grade students will report September 8 and continue 5 days a week. Students in grades 6 through 12 will continue to report on their assigned day per A/B schedules.

Sabine Online students should resume assignments if able. We are aware of power and internet issues due to storm damage. Information will be provided to all Sabine Online families this week. Students enrolled just prior to Hurricane Laura should have diagnostic assessments and courses. Any family planning to return to in-person classes should contact their school this week.

We look forward to seeing our students this week.

All Sabine Parish Schools will be closed through Monday, September 7, 2020, due to continued power outages and issues related to Hurricane Laura. This includes virtual/online learning students.

We plan to open schools, September 8, 2020. All Pre-K through 5th Grade students will report September 8 and continue 5 days a week. Students in grades 6 through 12 will continue to report on their assigned day per A/B schedules.

We are sensitive to the issues facing our families at this time. We are hopeful power and water will soon be restored to everyone.
Updates will be posted on our Facebook page.

post_text:
Sabine Parish Schools will welcome students back to school August 6th. Your child's teacher will be contacting you this week with your child’s schedule. Students will be divided into two groups. Group A will attend school on Tuesday and Thursday. Group B will attend school on Wednesday and Friday. Children living in the same household will be assigned to the same days. Monday is a dedicated distance-learning day in which teachers will report to school to deliver lessons, provide feedback, and prepare any materials needed for students.

If you have any questions after hearing from your child’s teacher, please contact your child’s school.

Sabine Online K-12 will be available to families interested in a full-time online setting instead of returning in-person. Please contact your school by July 20, 2020 if you are interested in Sabine Online.

There is still time to complete the Census 2020 questionnaire. It’s important for Sabine Parish!

“It's quick and easy. The 2020 Census questionnaire will take about 10 minutes to complete.
It's safe, secure, and confidential. Your information and privacy are protected.
Your response helps to direct billions of dollars in federal funds to local communities for schools, roads, and other public services.
Results from the 2020 Census will be used to determine the number of seats each state has in Congress and your political representation at all levels of government.”

Sabine’s goal is to reopen our schools so that students can return. We miss our students and are so ready to get them back to school. To ensure their safety there is much to consider so students can return to campuses. Local, regional, state, and federal organizations, working together, provide the guidance we must follow to start school.
SPSB is planning for different models to starting school and will know more closer to the August 6th scheduled start date. We are also offering a full online program for the 2020-2021 school year that was in development prior to the health crisis.
The linked state document is updated frequently to provide the guidance for every Louisiana school district to have a “Strong Start” for the 2020-2021 school year.

https://www.louisianabelieves.com/docs/default-source/strong-start-2020/school-reopening-guidelines-and-resources.pdf

The distribution will begin at 12:30 p.m. in Hornbeck at the office of Representative Rodney Schamerhorn located on 171 next to the post office. In Pleasant Hill we are hoping to serve Converse and the surrounding communities. In Zwolle we are hoping to serve Ebarb and the surrounding communities. Please see Representative Schamerhorn's Facebook page for schedule and any updates on schedule changes.

shared_text:
Sara Peace Ebarb
April 15 at 10:21 AM ·

Dear Seniors,
In honor of you, here is my senior picture from 1979, 41 years ago, Negreet High School. I know you are disappointed that your senior year has been cut short. My heart goes out to you all, but we are still planning on proms, athletic banquets, and graduation ceremonies as soon as it is safe. Your principals want you to have these experiences and so do I. We are proud of you and your accomplishments and understand your disappointment. Your senior year is a milestone, and the decisions you make from this point on will impact the rest of your life. You all are in a unique position to learn from this national crisis and to build your life around what is good, productive, secure and right; because through this, you have learned what really matters! Count your blessings, realize you are a blessing, and continue to be a blessing to someone everyday!
Sabine Proud,
Sara P. Ebarb, EdD
Your Superintendent

post_text:
National 4‑H Week is October 6 – 12 and the theme is "Inspire Kids to Do".
Take advantage of this important week to highlight the remarkable 4‑H youth in your communities and showcase the incredible experiences that 4‑H offers young people.

We are asking that area businesses and mayors help us paint the town green.

Please help us spotlight 4-H this week by doing proclamations for your schools, window art, signs, posters, and anything that would highlight Sabine Parish 4-H! We will be taking pictures and hosting a social media blitz with Facebook and Instagram. Our parish hashtag for this week will be #SabineNational4HWeek19 Let's see what you have!

Sell cupcakes, pickle pops, and green popcorn! Have a blast. Let 4-Her's make announcements.

Let's show everyone why it's great to be in 4-H. Our kids are our future.

Nan Arthur,
4-H Extension Agent
LSU AgCenter

post_text:
Louisiana GEAR UP and Northwestern State University will be hosting 4 different summer camp opportunities for rising 6th-10th graders (rising 7th-10th graders for Zwolle) in Sabine Parish during the month of July. Each camp will be a 5 day camp which will expose students to different careers and postsecondary education opportunities in the science, medical, and robotic fields. These non-residential camps are provided at NO COST to the students or parents and includes free transportation. All materials will be provided to students including t-shirts, bags, and snacks. Lunch will also be provided to students.
Registration is required for the camp and may be completed at http://www.lgusummercamps.osfa.la.gov/. Parents may register using either an active email address or cell phone number. If you have any additional questions about the camps or registration process, please call 225-627-3814.

Thank you!

Liz

Sabine Parish School Board
August 6, 2018 at 3:00 PM ·

Public Service Announcement:

Local and Parish law enforcement along with school administrators and staff are conducting a school emergency drill at MHS on Thursday, August 9th from 8:00 until approximately noon. The purpose of this drill is to provide important training for law enforcement, school leaders, and staff in order to keep students and staff safe in the event of an emergency. The drill will be conducted as a real emergency so do not be alarmed if you hear information on emergency scanners or see police at the campus. Please do not attempt to approach any of the Many school campuses during the drill.
We appreciate your cooperation.

UPDATE: Sabine Parish Students’ Drama Club performing at The Sabine Theater

Tonight, May 4th at 7:00 and Sunday, May 6th at 2:00
shared_text:
Linda Cox Boudreaux
April 22, 2018 at 7:56 AM ·

Sabine Parish Schools Drama Club is preforming this fun spoof on May 4and 6. Mark your calendars and don’t miss it! These are some very bright and talented students who have worked hard outside of their regular school requirements. Please come and support their efforts.

The schools will dismiss early on the following dates to allow students and staff time to travel to Sulphur.

Ebarb High School—Thursday, April 26 at 1:30
Converse High Scool— Friday, April 27 at 11:30
Florien High School—Friday, April 27 at 12:00
Many Schools—Friday, April 27 at 2:00
